[SourceTitle "01 King's Gambit"]
[Source "Chessable.com"]
[Comment "1e4-e5-a-comprehensive-black-repertoire-against-1e4/course/3767, variation/120860"]

1. e4 e5 2. f4 {The King's Gambit is a very feared weapon at lower levels of 
chess. It is a romantic opening that has been played for decades, and it 
deserves lots of respect. However, Black should not have much trouble equalizing 
against it with good play.} exf4 {I think it is best to simply grab the pawn 
because they are worried that going right into the main line is a risky choice. 
However, it is also the most testing choice and Black can equalize.} 3. Nf3 {Nf3 
is the main move, avoiding Qh4+ ideas.} g5 {g5 is the main line and the biggest 
test of the the king's gambit's validity. Black supports his pawn of f4.} 4. d4 
{White seizes the center.} g4 {Black continues to push forward with his g-pawn.} 
5. Bxf4 gxf3 {A piece is a piece. :)} 6. Qxf3 Nc6 7. Bc4 Qf6 {White's 
compensation is not sufficient.} *

