immediately attacking the e5 pawn, White chooses to simply support his pawn on 
e4.} Nf6 {Simply developing the kingside knight is best.} 3. f4 {f4 is most in 
the spirit of the Vienna Game, but it is nothing to fear.} d5 {d5 is the 
thematic counter-thrust in the center that one has to remember.} 4. fxe5 {fxe5 
is the best choice and by far the most popular, but exd5 is also possible.} Nxe4 
