{d4 is a critical move that provokes many weaknesses in White's camp.} 7. Nf3 
{Nf3 is the only logical move, developing a piece and hitting the d4 pawn.} Nc6 
{Black continues to develop with a very decent position.} 8. Be2 {White 
continues to develop and prepares to castle.} Bc5 9. O-O dxc3+ {Now Black has an 
extra pawn, but the c3 pawn is weak and will likely be recovered by White.} 10. 
Kh1 O-O {Black can claim a pleasant edge.} 11. Qe1 *

