square around White's king after he castles.} 7. Nf3 {White quietly develops. I 
enjoy answering this move with Be7+Bf6, and it is very hard for White to find 
any kind of advantage.} Be7 8. O-O O-O 9. Re1 Bf6 {The point of Be7. The bishop 
on f6 makes it very hard for White to achieve the desired d4 push.} 10. Rb1 Rb8 
