1. e4 e5 2. d4 {2. d4 often leads to a variety of possible gambit lines. White 
can also simply recapture the pawn on d4, which is called the center game.} exd4 
{Capturing the d4 pawn is simply the only logical choice.} 3. Qxd4 {The Center 
Game. White immediately recovers his pawn. The drawback to this opening by White 
is that his queen is vulnerable and hence Black can develop with tempo.} Nc6 
{Black develops and wins a tempo on the queen.} 4. Qa4 Bb4+ 5. c3 Bc5 {Black is 
doing very well. White's knight cannot develop to c3.} *

