by simply advancing his d-pawn to the center. That is a very good way of 
playing.} 4. exd5 {exd5 is the main line. White will be left with an unwanted 
isolated pawn that Black can later put pressure on.} Qxd5 5. cxd4 Nc6 {Both the 
knight and the queen are hitting d4.} 6. Be3 Bb4+ 7. Nc3 Nf6 8. Nf3 Qa5 {Black 
is very active.} *

