Nxc6 bxc6 {Taking with the d-pawn would be an error as it allows Qxd8+.} 7. Bd3 
{Bd3 is by far the most common move as White needs to castle sooner rather than 
later.} d5 {d5 is an important move to remember as it allow Black to free his 
position and fight for the center. d6 is also interesting, but not as strong.} 
8. exd5 {White has nothing better than to trade on d5.} cxd5 9. O-O {White 
castles to bring his king out of the center.} O-O 10. h3 {Kramnik has toyed with 
this idea. h3 stops Bg4 so that Qf3 can be played.} c6 11. Qf3 Re8 {Black takes 
control of the e-file.} 12. Bf4 Bd6 {The position is about equal.} *

