{Black has to take the pawn.} 6. cxd4 {White will usually take back and force 
the bishop to move. However, White can also try e5 or O-O instead.} Bb4+ {Bb4+ 
is the only way to challenge White's center. Now White has a few ways in which 
he can block the check.} 7. Nbd2 {Nbd2 is a fairly uncommon sideline.} d5 {Black 
begins to break up White's center.} 8. exd5 Nxd5 {Black takes back on d5.} 9. 
O-O O-O 10. a3 Be7 {Black is in good shape.} *

