undermine the b5 pawn early on.} Bd7 {Black develops his bishop to d7, a logical 
choice.} 9. c3 O-O 10. d4 {White grabs the center.} h6 11. Nbd2 Re8 {Now White 
has two options: Nf1 and the more committal d5.} 12. Nf1 Bf8 {Black has ideas of 
g6 followed by Bg7 with a very solid position. Na5 followed by c5 is also very 
logical.} *

